Track is going awesome, i love hurdles and high jump. Ran 2.25 miles in new shoes friday, not a good idea, arches were killing me.

Basketball game today, first ever, i hate how the coach favors his son, when he sucks worse than I do. Yeah. We got whooped, like 45-60. Oh well, maybe we should actually make some plays?

Yeah.

Everyone went to a movie tonight and my mom made me stay home and do homework, oh well.

Track all this week, i'm loving it. JUST NOT STAIRS!

Holy crap.


Track today, had to run 2 miles, i didn't do too horribly, but it was a shock for me i haven't run that far in a long long time.


Tomorrow is going to suck.

English project due Thursday that i haven't started, tomorrow i have jazz til 4:30, then track til 6 after that, then basketball 7:30-9 after that.

Wow.

Today was awesome.


Sub in Science, very happy  because i didn't do my lap report.

Math, i actually knew something for once, Quadratic formula haha. 

English, as retarded as always.

Freshman Seminar, uhm, it's freshman seminar, can it be good at all?

After school was track, track is going to be 2:30-4 weight room, then 4-6 training, running, jumping.

Track is going to be awesome, i can tell already it's going to be very very fun, and hopefully i'll be good at it.

I have mass amounts of homework, so that sucks, but today rocked, and Track capped it off.

Today was OK. 


Woke up like 12, had people over for football at 3, which the pats won 24-3, wasn't a good game though. 


Mom freaked out on me and called a huge family meeting because of the way people acted when they were over here. Not a big deal, just guys, if you come over, don't talk to my siblings at all, no conversation, it helps a lot, and i've learned if i don't want to get in trouble, don't talk to them.

Played a little bit of UT, and now i'm here. 

I REALLY don't want to write my English poem, or the English project, or the Math project which i have NO IDEA what is going on with. 

Oh well.

Just got home from greg's party, it was fun, coulda been more fun but whatever. 

Bored, and i don't want to do the stupid english poem or project, or the math project.


Ugh.

Thanksgiving was fun, i went to my aunt's house and ate, and saw all my relatives. Played some poker too and got my ass handed to me, i don't know, you can't do anything if you don't get the cards. 

Today i was home all day, was going to go play football but decided not to, so some people came to my house, hung out for a bit, and now i'm here.


Yeah, nothing exciting, Greg's party is tomorrow so it should be fun.

Today was boring.

Woke up at like 11, went and got a haircut at 12:30, cut one of my sideburns too short, but whatever.

Downloaded and watched Super Troopers. Mother of god. The Snozberries taste like Snozberries!

Went to basketball practice at 8, i will have to say basketball has to be one of the most fun things, EVER. Got home at 9:30, and i've been on the computer since. 

And now i think i'll eat mass amounts of Ramen Noodles, and go to bed.

Seeya.

Pep rally today, mildly annoying because none of the freshman were doing anything. 

No on would start the wave, and that made me sad.

Oh well. 


Boring ass day, just like every other day.

I think i did decently on my math test, thank GOD for graphing calculators though holy crap.

Yeah, got home from school awhile ago, weight room was closed so i didn't go to it and had to bother my mom for a ride home, took Torin home, almost broke the car on those damn speed bumps in Coburn Woods, haha.

We flew our hot air balloons in Science, our's won, yeah paige, OUR'S WON.  

Math was nothing but recursive functions

English was gay, IE, Mr. Carlos, read some of the Odyssey, not terrible, just hard to put all together in your head. 

Freshman Seminar, didn't do much except talk about the couple of people that died over the weekend in those car crashes, that sucks. 

Yeah so hopefully i'll go to Karaoke tonight, that should be a hoot. 

Cousin came and visited today after school, always nice seeing Katie, they're all at the Elm Street Girls basketball game right now, and i'm chilling at home listening to music by myself, one o fmy favorite things to do i would say.

Mmmmmm, uncooked ramen!

Dinner conversation

Elizabeth: Can everyone be quiet please i have a headache.
(everyone talks quietly)

Elizabeth: CAN EVERYONE BE QUIET PLEASE I HAVE A HEADACHE!

(mom gets a phone call from a family friend who is in the hospital)

Mom: (talking to the friend) How are you doing? (and such)

Elizabeth: CAN YOU PLEASE BE QUIET I HAVE A HEADACHE!

Mom starts on a speech for something other than Elizabeth i can't remember what.

Me: I love how the hierarchy in this house goes Elizabeth-Mom Dad- Everyone else

Elizabeth: CAN YOU PLEASE BE QUIET I HAVE A HEADACHE! AND THAT'S NOT TRUE!

Dad: Elizabeth, if you can't take it leave.

Me: No, I can't take it anymore. ::leaves::

I know how it is to have a headache, i get a lot of headaches, but at the dinner table? Suck it up! She makes me so mad, jesus, she talks to my mother like she owns her, what the hell is her problem anyway? 

I know my place, i know who i must respect, and who i can talk on an equal level with. Elizabeth, she thinks she owns the world, biggest hypocrit ever.

If she died i would laugh.

Sunday- Mother's day, woke up in a crappy ass mood and argued to not go to my baseball practice, i was wrong, went to baseball, pretty fun there actually, came home, played basketball all day and hung out with my mom!

Weekend was pretty good actually, busy, and i got no sleep, but good.

Listen to this, guys. This morning during our day off I was online and decided to play a game. Instead of putting up a dumb away messege like, "Playing Game" I decided to look at my creative ability. I put up an away messege as follows, " I am mad at you n%" (In cas you don't have aol instant messenger n% enters the name of the screename of the person looking at the away messege/profile/whatever) And Michelle looks at it and takes it personally, and leaves me over 65 freakin' messeges like, "joe, answer me", "I know you're there Joe", and "Why are you mad at me Joe" So I get off of my game and tell her that i just put n% and she doesn't comprehend whatever the hell it means. So about an hour ago she calls my house to ask me why I'm mad at her, and at this point I'm like, "Why can't she just drop it" and she still doesn't understand what I'm talking about, so right now Michelle thinks that I am mad at her. The only adjectives I can use to describe this situation are, "Oblivious, thick-skulled, and Dumbass (Darzee)" Please comment on this bizzare situation, Originally by Joe
